One of the great years of our generation. Rich in fruit and charm, these wines have matured relatively quickly. All are showing great attractiveness even for present drinking, but we do believe a year or two more of bottle age will bring a reward to the more patient wine drinker, particularly when the great vineyards are involved. The price level of these wines are relatively stabilized in relation to the ’59s, 61s and ’62s, which are dramatically soaring on the market place of Bordeaux. However, all evidence indicates that the ’64s will go up substantially during the latter part of 1968.
